{"type":"message","id":"1a89c2bc","parentId":"ae1666ed","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:21:32.898Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771168892872_400","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 🤖 DMarket Telegram Bot\n\n![GitHub release (latest by date)](https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot?style=flat-square)\n![GitHub Workflow Status](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/ci.yml?style=flat-square&label=CI)\n![GitHub License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot?style=flat-square)\n\n> **Enterprise-grade automation** for DMarket interaction, featuring sub-millisecond latency and robust multiprocessing architecture.\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Performance Stats\n\n| Metric | Value |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **Latency** | `0.0368ms` |\n| **Active Skills** | `40` |\n| **Coverage** | `100%` |\n\n---\n\n## 🏗️ Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    Master[Master Process] <--> Redis[(Redis Cache)]\n    Redis <--> W1[Worker 1]\n    Redis <--> W2[Worker 2]\n    Redis <--> W3[Worker 3]\n    Redis <--> W4[Worker 4]\n    \n    style Master fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style Redis fill:#ff9,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n```\n\n## 📜 Version History\n\n*   **v2.1:** Docker, GHCR, Enterprise CI/CD.\n*   **v2.0:** Multiprocessing, 40 Skills, 0.03ms Latency.\n*   **v1.0:** SACS-2026, Ed25519, Hot Reload.\n*   **v0.1:** Legacy script (Broken Async).\n\n## 🎮 Commands\n\n### General\n*   👋 `/start` - Initialize the bot interaction.\n*   ❓ `/help` - Show available commands.\n*   📊 `/status` - Check system health and uptime.\n*   ⚙️ `/settings` - Configure bot preferences.\n\n### Trading\n*   💰 `/balance` - View current DMarket balance.\n*   📦 `/inventory` - List items in inventory.\n*   📉 `/price <item>` - Check price for a specific item.\n*   🛒 `/buy <item>` - Initiate a buy order.\n*   🏷️ `/sell <item>` - Initiate a sell order.\n\n### Automation\n*   🤖 `/auto_buy` - Toggle auto-buy module.\n*   🔄 `/auto_sell` - Toggle auto-sell module.\n*   📜 `/history` - View transaction history.\n*   🛑 `/stop` - Emergency stop all active tasks.\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Deployment\n\n### Docker (Recommended)\n\n```bash\ndocker pull ghcr.io/dykij/dmarket-telegram-bot:latest\ndocker run -d --env-file .env ghcr.io/dykij/dmarket-telegram-bot:latest\n```\n\n### Manual\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot.git\ncd DMarket-Telegram-Bot\npip install -r requirements.txt\npython main.py\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771168892896}}
{"type":"message","id":"7aa21518","parentId":"1a89c2bc","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:21:40.584Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing README.md Revisions**\n\nI'm focused on restructuring the `README.md` file, with the aim of incorporating modifications into its format and content. My initial step involves updating the license information, specifically adjusting the copyright to reflect \"Dykij\". Following this, I will move on to the more extensive rewrite of the `README.md` itself, starting with replacing existing badges.\n\n\n**Implementing README Revisions**\n\nI'm making progress. I've successfully updated the license and am now focusing on the `README.md` rewrite. I've begun integrating the new badges into the header and am now working on the performance dashboard comparison table. Next, I'll incorporate descriptions for the AI stack components before updating the architecture diagram.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771168900583_401","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"MIT License\n\nCopyright (c) 2024 Dykij\n\nPermission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy\nof this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal\nin the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights\nto use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell\ncopies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is\nfurnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:\n\nThe above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all\ncopies or substantial portions of the Software.\n\nTHE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR\nIMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,\nFITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE\nAUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER\nLIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,\nOUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE\nSOFTWARE.","file_path":"LICENSE"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":9127,"output":404,"cacheRead":8278,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9531,"cost":{"input":0.018254,"output":0.004848,"cacheRead":0.0016556000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.024757599999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771168892899}}
